\section{Introduction}

This report explains the design, development, and content of my personal computer science portfolio, which was created as part of the Computer Science Lab assessment. The main aim of this project was to build a professional portfolio website that presents my technical skills, academic achievements, personal projects, and career goals in a clear and organised way. The website was designed to help future employers learn more about my abilities and experience.

As part of the project, I also created a professional CV using LaTeX. This helped me produce a well formatted and professional looking document while improving my understanding of LaTeX. In addition, all project files were organised in a structured GitHub repository. This allowed me to manage my work properly, keep track of changes, and follow good software development practices. Overall, this project helped me improve both my technical skills and my ability to present my work in a professional way.


The portfolio serves as a digital representation of my skills and experiences as a first year BSc Software Engineering student at Gisma University of Applied Sciences in Berlin. It brings together key aspects of my academic journey, including coursework, technical projects, and practical learning experiences. The website also highlights my early professional experience, demonstrating how I have developed important workplace skills such as communication, teamwork, responsibility, and problem solving.



